isoiec80000:term-t10-11-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "total angular momentum"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t10-11-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "bb(ii(J))"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t10-11 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "10-11" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t10-11-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t10-11-0 ;
  skos:definition """vector (<<iso80000-2>>) quantity in a quantum system composed of the vectorial sum of angular momentum stem:[bb(ii(L))] (<<iso80000-4>>) and spin stem:[bb(ii(s))] (<<t10-10>>)"""@en ;
  skos:note """In atomic and nuclear physics, orbital angular momentum is usually denoted by stem:[bb(ii(l))] or stem:[bb(ii(L))].

The magnitude of stem:[bb(ii(J))] is quantized so that:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
bb(ii(J))^2 = &#8463;^2 j(j+1)
++++

where stem:[j] is the total angular momentum quantum number (<<t10-13.6>>).

Total angular momentum and magnetic dipole moment have the same direction.

stem:[j] is not the magnitude of the total angular momentum stem:[bb(ii(J))] but its projection onto the quantization axis, divided by stem:[&#8463;].
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J*s ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-eV*s ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^2*s^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-10 .